The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Funds for CU law school
                                                                                                               Funds for CU law school
                            
	Calcutta, July 18: Both the state and the Centre today promised funds for the upgrade of the University College of Law, Calcutta, at the inauguration of its centenary celebrations.        
	State finance minister Asim Dasgupta promised a purse for a centenary chair named after Ashutosh Mookerjee and said: We would also like to provide for two research fellowships and five student fellowships for the needy.         
	The state will also fund the upgrade of the institutes library and renovation of its Hazra Road building. Calcutta University wants to add two floors to its six-storey law school.        
	Union finance minister Pranab Mukherjee, the chief guest, asked the vice-chancellor to submit at the earliest a funds proposal focused on research and development. Ill make a special package, said Mukherjee, an alumnus.                                                                                                                                                                              
